---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/information-page.scss";
---

<BaseLayout
  locale="en"
  title="Privacy and data handling | IzignaMx"
  description="Information about diagnostic data, analytics, local storage, and IzignaMx privacy channels."
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy/"
  alternatePath="/es/privacidad/"
>
  <article class="information-page" data-pagefind-body>
    <header class="information-page__header">
      <p class="information-page__eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Minimum data, explicit decisions.</h1>
      <p class="information-page__intro">
        This page describes the Capability Book’s current technical behavior and the conditions
        that must be met before direct diagnostic delivery is enabled.
      </p>
      <p class="information-page__status">Updated: July 21, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="information-page__sections">
      <section aria-labelledby="current-state-title">
        <h2 id="current-state-title">Current state</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p class="information-page__notice">
            <strong>Direct form delivery is disabled.</strong> GitHub Pages serves this site as
            static files, and its HTTPS does not create a form backend. If you choose the email
            fallback, data leaves through your email client and provider.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before an external service is enabled, its identity, location, subprocessors,
            transfers, retention periods, and deletion procedure will be published.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="diagnostic-data-title">
        <h2 id="diagnostic-data-title">Diagnostic data</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>The form may request:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>name, contact method, organization or project, and request;</li>
            <li>optionally: current URL, timing, budget, integrations, and references;</li>
            <li>consent and non-personal source context such as route, project, capability, service, and approved UTM parameters;</li>
            <li>an empty honeypot field to help detect automation.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Until sent, the draft remains only in that tab’s <code>sessionStorage</code> and is
            removed after confirmed delivery. Context and server responses are not stored in the
            draft.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="analytics-title">
        <h2 id="analytics-title">Excluded from analytics</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>
            Product analytics must not receive names, email addresses, telephone numbers,
            organizations, messages, form content, or personal identifiers. The measurement plan
            permits only predefined events and non-personal context dimensions.
          </p>
          <p>
            The site currently initializes no product analytics or advertising trackers. If
            analytics compatible with this plan is activated, planned retention is 30 days for
            non-personal raw events and 395 days for aggregates.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="infrastructure-title">
        <h2 id="infrastructure-title">Infrastructure</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>
            The site is published on GitHub Pages. As the hosting provider, GitHub may process
            technical request data under its own terms and policies. IzignaMx does not use those
            logs as diagnostic content or for advertising profiles.
          </p>
          <p>
            Session storage remains local to the browser. The current implementation uses no
            advertising cookies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="rights-title">
        <h2 id="rights-title">Questions and rights</h2>
        <div class="information-page__copy">
          <p>
            For privacy questions or access, correction, deletion, or objection requests, email
            <a href="mailto:hola@izignamx.com?subject=Capability%20Book%20privacy">hola@izignamx.com</a>.
            Describe the request without adding unnecessary information.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before direct collection is enabled, production review must complete the responsible
            party and applicable provider’s legal details. This technical transparency does not
            replace that legal review.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
